meanings.definition: To surpass in rock music performance.
meanings.sent1: The band outrocked all others at the concert.
meanings.sent2: She outrocked her competition with her amazing guitar skills.
meanings.sent3: The guitarist outrocked everyone so much that they all wanted her autograph.
meanings.sent4: His energetic performance outrocked the audience, leaving them in awe.
meanings.sent5: The rock star outrocked all expectations with his electrifying show.

meanings.definition: To outdo or outperform in a rock music context.
meanings.sent1: The new album outrocked their previous releases.
meanings.sent2: The band outrocked themselves with their latest hit single.
meanings.sent3: The drummer outrocked everyone by playing with his eyes closed.
meanings.sent4: Her vocals outrocked the entire band, stealing the show.
meanings.sent5: The guitarist outrocked the competition, proving he was the best in town.
